        <h2>1. Buildertrend — Best project tracking for residential builders</h2>
        <p><strong>Price:</strong> $499–$1,099/mo</p>

        <p>Buildertrend's project tracking centers on three things: budget vs. actual, schedule against the Gantt baseline, and progress photos tied to tasks. The budget module pulls in your original estimate, tracks committed costs (approved change orders, POs) and actual costs (bills entered or synced from QuickBooks), and shows you in real time how far off budget each cost category is running.</p>

        <p>The schedule tracking is equally strong — you can see whether tasks are completed on time, which ones are running late, and how delays are cascading to downstream tasks with automatic dependency updates. For residential builders managing 5–30 simultaneous projects, the cross-project dashboard view is particularly valuable for spotting which projects need attention.</p>

